    • Method Detail

      • testOp

        protected void testOp(String[] dataSample)
        Tests an unary function on Quadruple.
        Creates a DataItem instance with the source value expressed as Quadruple and BigDecimal values, performs the tested operation and creates a DataItem with the result, creates a DataItem with the expected value of the result, then registers the result in the TestResults instance stored in the corresponding field using its TestResults.record(DataItem, DataItem, DataItem) method.
        Specified by:
        testOp in class TesterClasses.QuadTester
        Parameters:
        dataSample - an array containing String representations of the input argument(s) of the tested operation and a string representation of the expected result
